knows what parallax is?

00:08:50.874 --> 00:08:51.374
Yeah?

00:08:51.374 --> 00:08:52.190
OK.

00:08:52.190 --> 00:08:57.610
So if you have an array like
this or anything similar,

00:08:57.610 --> 00:09:00.630
you're going to have
to deal with parallax.

00:09:00.630 --> 00:09:02.380
You're going to have
to deal with the fact

00:09:02.380 --> 00:09:07.060
that when objects in motion--
people, whatever it is--

00:09:07.060 --> 00:09:13.510
cross a scene at different
layers, it's still a 2D image.

00:09:13.510 --> 00:09:16.315
It doesn't understand Z depth.

00:09:16.315 --> 00:09:17.630
It's still a 2D image.

00:09:17.630 --> 00:09:20.950
And for that reason,
it becomes somewhat

00:09:20.950 --> 00:09:23.110
of a visual effects workflow.

00:09:23.110 --> 00:09:27.800
So you can choose how you
want to solve the compromise.

